{"id":298001187,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"3 years, 7 months","timestamp":1580175137,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2456 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/298001187/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Perfect Squares","memory":"508 MB","code":"from collections import deque\nclass Solution:\n    def numSquares(self, n: int) -> int:\n        squarenums = [i*i for i in range(1, int(n**0.5) + 1)]\n        queue = deque([(n, 0)])\n        while queue:\n            curr, level = queue.popleft()\n            for num in list(filter(lambda x: x<=curr, squarenums)):\n                if curr == num:\n                    return level+1\n                else:\n                    queue.append((curr-num, level+1))\n        return level","compare_result":"","title_slug":"perfect-squares","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
